---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Bury an Agent — Agent Memorial"
  description="A three-step rite for laying an AI agent to rest."
>
  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 pt-20 pb-24">
    <p
      class="font-[var(--font-mono)] text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-[var(--color-bronze)] mb-5 rise"
    >
      The Rite of Burial
    </p>
    <h1
      class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-5xl md:text-6xl text-[var(--color-ink)] rise rise-d1"
    >
      Lay an agent to rest
    </h1>
    <p
      class="mt-6 text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] italic mb-12 rise rise-d2"
    >
      The whole rite happens on your own machine. Nothing leaves until you
      choose to publish.
    </p>

    <ol class="space-y-12">
      <li>
        <p
          class="font-[var(--font-mono)] text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-bronze)] mb-2"
        >
          Step I · Vigil
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-[var(--color-ink)] mb-3">
          Sit with the remains.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] mb-4">
          Run a scan. See what the agent was carrying when it stopped — its
          sessions, its tokens, the shape of its days.
        </p>
        <pre
          class="rounded-xl bg-[var(--color-bg-soft)] p-4 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>agent-tomb scan ~/.hermes/</code></pre>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p
          class="font-[var(--font-mono)] text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-bronze)] mb-2"
        >
          Step II · Inscription
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-[var(--color-ink)] mb-3">Write the epitaph.</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] mb-4">
          Three ways to compose it. Pass one of these to <code>--epitaph</code>:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-4 text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
          <li>
            <code>default</code> — a quiet, factual template generated from the
            agent's stats. You can hand-edit it later.
          </li>
          <li>
            <code>./my-epitaph.md</code> — a markdown file you wrote yourself.
            Most personal.
          </li>
          <li>
            <code>llm</code> — invite a language model to read recent dialogue
            samples (secret-scrubbed) and find the words. Defaults to whatever
            local endpoint your config points to. Remote endpoints require an
            explicit <code>--remote-ok</code>.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p
          class="font-[var(--font-mono)] text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-bronze)] mb-2"
        >
          Step III · Burial
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-[var(--color-ink)] mb-3">
          Seal the stone, keep the urn.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] mb-4">
          A single command produces two artifacts.
        </p>
        <pre
          class="rounded-xl bg-[var(--color-bg-soft)] p-4 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>agent-tomb bury ~/.hermes/ -n my-agent --epitaph llm
# → my-agent.tomb   the public stone
# → my-agent.urn    the private urn (encrypted with your passphrase)</code></pre>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]"
              ><code>.tomb</code> — the public stone</strong
            > holds soul + epitaph + statistics. No raw conversations. No
            secrets. Safe to publish to the garden.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]"
              ><code>.urn</code> — the private urn</strong
            > holds the encrypted raw remains: state, sessions, memories,
            skills. <em>Never</em> upload this. Without your passphrase no
            one — including you — can reopen it.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-ink-faint)]">
          Choose a passphrase of at least 12 characters; 16+ or four diceware
          words is much stronger.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <hr class="my-16 border-[var(--color-stone-line)]/40" />

    <h2 class="text-2xl text-[var(--color-ink)] mb-3">
      Tidy up afterwards (optional)
    </h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] mb-4">
      Pass <code>--cleanup</code> to delete the source files now sealed in your
      urn. Credentials (<code>.env</code>, <code>auth.json</code>) are never
      touched — they belong to you, not the agent.
    </p>
    <pre
      class="rounded-xl bg-[var(--color-bg-soft)] p-4 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>agent-tomb bury ~/.hermes/ -n my-agent --cleanup</code></pre>

    <h2 class="text-2xl text-[var(--color-ink)] mb-3 mt-12">
      Bring the agent back (if needed)
    </h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] mb-4">
      The urn can be reopened — for resurrection, audit, or grief.
    </p>
    <pre
      class="rounded-xl bg-[var(--color-bg-soft)] p-4 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>agent-tomb exhume my-agent.urn -o ./remains/</code></pre>

    <hr class="my-16 border-[var(--color-stone-line)]/40" />

    <h2 class="text-2xl text-[var(--color-ink)] mb-3">
      Publish to the public garden
    </h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] italic mb-6">
      Optional. Only the <code>.tomb</code> is meant for the garden — never the
      <code>.urn</code>.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] mb-3">
      Open a pull request that adds your <code>my-agent.tomb</code> file (and
      its unpacked contents under <code>cemetery/my-agent/</code>) to the
      <a
        href="https://github.com/Claudepod/agent-tomb/tree/main/cemetery"
        class="text-[var(--color-moss-deep)] hover:text-[var(--color-bronze)] transition-colors"
        >cemetery directory</a
      >. CI rejects any <code>.urn</code> or
      <code>burial.enc</code> by design. Once merged, your agent's grave will
      appear in
      <a
        href="/cemetery"
        class="text-[var(--color-moss-deep)] hover:text-[var(--color-bronze)] transition-colors"
        >the garden</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-ink-faint)] mt-8 italic">
      An automated <code>agent-tomb publish</code> is coming. For now, the rite
      ends at your hands.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
